verse.lines:
{lang-eng}My country, ‘tis of Thee,
Sweet land of liberty, of Thee I sing;
Land where my fathers died,
Land of the pilgrims’ pride,
From every mountain side let freedom ring!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}My native country, thee,
Land of the noble, free, thy name I love;
I love thy rocks and rills,
Thy woods and templed hills,
My heart with rapture thrills like that above.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Let music swell the breeze,
And ring from all the trees sweet freedom’s song;
Let mortal tongues awake;
Let all that breathe partake;
Let rocks their silence break, the sound prolong.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Our fathers’ God, to thee,
Author of liberty, to thee we sing;
Long may our land be bright
With freedom’s holy light,
Protect us by Thy might, Great God our King!{/lang-eng}
